		  <div class="__pf" id="__pf"><div class="pf-0e65165e sc-hwwEjo kIFSBP" data-pf-type="Body"><div class="pf-8c2ecbfb sc-kUaPvJ gjMMZr" data-pf-type="Layout"><div data-container="true" class="pf-1a508e18 sc-kLIISr lgZhBD" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-dliRfk gThRmc" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="pf-45495da1 pf-r pf-r-eh pf-r-ew sc-ipXKqB ciNxzc" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12" style="padding: 15px;"><div class="pf-261955dc sc-fONwsr BcUQo" data-pf-type="Column"><h1 mode="view" class="pf-ec1bfc94 sc-epnACN iUKiYr" data-pf-type="Heading"><span class="pf-af1ae36d sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">Is it Safe to give CBD to Children</span></h1><h2 mode="view" class="pf-1197c320 sc-hXRMBi htgpzE" data-pf-type="Heading"><span class="pf-8189f4d3 sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">Can you give CBD to kids?</span></h2></div></div></div><div class="pf-a7e30886 pf-r pf-r-eh pf-r-ew sc-ipXKqB ciNxzc" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12" style="padding: 15px;"><div class="pf-49415828 sc-fONwsr BcUQo" data-pf-type="Column"><h3 mode="view" class="pf-caf0e626 sc-gwVKww jSNcIx" data-pf-type="Heading"><span class="pf-68de828b sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">Becky Spencer-Davies&nbsp;</span></h3></div></div></div><div class="pf-52c775fa pf-r pf-r-eh pf-r-ew sc-ipXKqB ciNxzc" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12" style="padding: 15px;"><div class="pf-0c0a5232 sc-fONwsr BcUQo" data-pf-type="Column"><p class="pf-8d591ca1 dropcap--none sc-ebFjAB ebQNGs" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span class="pf-11876db5 sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">T</span><span class="pf-c03e18e0 sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">he health of your child is most likely one of your highest priorities. So when you see that a cannabinoid which comes from the cannabis plant could help your child you might raise an eyebrow. Your first thought might be, isn’t cannabis illegal? Then you might wonder how a substance from this plant might help with various conditions and illnesses your child is suffering from.&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div></div><div class="pf-4c6d867b pf-r pf-r-eh sc-ipXKqB ciNxzc" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12" style="padding: 15px;"><div class="pf-05c400f9 sc-fONwsr BcUQo" data-pf-type="Column"><h3 mode="view" class="pf-3eff5c50 sc-gwVKww jSNcIx" data-pf-type="Heading"><span class="pf-52acec16 sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">What is CBD?<br></span></h3><p class="pf-b06f1902 sc-ebFjAB bLbPLR" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span class="pf-f3e0bd3a sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">CBD is a cannabinoid which comes from the cannabis plant. However, it is legal. This is because it doesn’t contain any THC, which is the psychoactive part of the plant. CBD will not give you or your child a ‘high’ or make them feel the same way THC might. CBD’s effects are purely therapeutic, without the negative side effects.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br></span></p><h3 mode="view" class="pf-ec97ffaf sc-gwVKww jSNcIx" data-pf-type="Heading"><span class="pf-2dba5e73 sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">Can you give CBD to children?<br></span></h3><p class="pf-4f7b605b sc-ebFjAB bLbPLR" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span class="pf-3d1432da sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">Yes, you can give <a href="https://vapeandjuice.co.uk/collections/cbd-oils">CBD</a> to children. However, you will need to deliver the dose to them. You might give CBD to your child to help them with a number of conditions they may suffer with. These conditions include:<br><br>- Pain<br>- Anxiety <br>- Epilepsy <br>- ADHD<br>- Autism<br><br>There have been studies which look at the effect of CBD on children suffering with conditions such as the above. You can read more about those <a href="https://www.hmhb.org/cbd-oil-for-kids/" target="_self">studies here</a>.<br></span></p><h3 mode="view" class="pf-1596fd12 sc-gwVKww jSNcIx" data-pf-type="Heading"><span class="pf-e986ff4c sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">How does CBD work?<br></span></h3><p class="pf-93aff775 sc-ebFjAB bLbPLR" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span class="pf-f413f04f sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">CBD is said to interact with the endocannabinoid system in the body. This interaction changes the way in which our cells perceive pain and makes serotonin more available to the body. The exact way in which CBD works is still being researched, however there is evidence and anecdotal evidence from parents which points in the right direction.<br></span></p><h3 mode="view" class="pf-fe0c4c32 sc-gwVKww jSNcIx" data-pf-type="Heading"><span class="pf-04d87226 sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">How can CBD be given to children?<br></span></h3><p class="pf-ee0fe1b8 sc-ebFjAB bLbPLR" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span class="pf-eba76893 sc-RcBXQ uIbp" data-pf-type="Text">There are many ways to take CBD, however some, such as vaping, wouldn’t be suitable for children. We suggest that you use CBD oil tincture drops or CBD gummies. The CBD gummies will be palatable and enjoyable for the child. When first giving your child CBD make sure that you start on a low dose and keep an eye on their tolerance to it. You can always increase the dosage going forward.<br><br>So, yes. It is safe to give your children CBD. Just as it is safe to give yourself and even your <a href="https://cbdstar.co/product/small-paws-250mg-full-spectrum-cbd-oil-for-pets-with-salmon-oil-by-cbd-leaf/" target="_self">pets CBD</a>.&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="pf-5bdf3575 sc-kLIISr lgZhBD" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-dliRfk gThRmc" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="pf-ac370011 pf-r pf-r-eh pf-r-ew sc-ipXKqB ciNxzc" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12" style="padding: 15px;"><div class="pf-e33c1834 sc-fONwsr BcUQo" data-pf-type="Column"><div class="pf-2711ec4a pr